            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Had a really bad experience with Step by step school Noida.. My daughter recently shifted from UK and we wanted her to join this school. Initially they asked for 2.5 hours of assessment for which no syllabus was defined and then they said she did not clear the written assessment . First of all they were not considerate of the fact that for past 2.5 years my daughter has not studied Hindi and they failed her which really affected my child then there admission councelor Shalini Joshi called us and told she is selected for round 2 on Friday, my daughter statted preparing for the Friday interview and on Friday when we called her again she said there must be some confusion that we told you to come for round 2. This was absolutely unethical at their end as my daughter was heart broken. I think this school only needs cream of students and don't want to put any effort in a student who wants to learn but due to her situation a little behind .",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
